snippet: The Municipal Transportation Agency of San Francisco said it had reached a tentative agreement on a new contract with its union.
abstract: Municipal Transportation Agency of San Francisco reaches tentative agreement on new contract with its union, whose workers took part in sickout that stalled the city's cable cars and disrupted other services; terms of the deal have not been disclosed.
lead_paragraph: The Municipal Transportation Agency of San Francisco said it had reached a tentative agreement on a new contract with its union.
